## Why This Is Asked
Explores practical RT-level data governance in OTCA: retention, holds, residency, and auditability across regions.

## Key Concepts
- Per-tenant policy store; region-scoped purges
- Data tagging: retention_version, tombstones
- Holds vs purge: immutable logs, legal holds
- Storage: object-lock Parquet; Kafka retention
- Testing: synthetic holds, burst scenarios, cross-region audits

## Code Example
```javascript
// Simple eligibility check for purge
function eligibleForPurge(record, policy, currentDate) {
  const byTenant = policy.tenant_id === record.tenant_id;
  const byRegion = policy.region === record.region;
  const ageDays = (currentDate - new Date(record.createdAt)) / (1000*60*60*24);
  const notOnHold = !record.hold_id || !policy.hold_ids.includes(record.hold_id);
  return byTenant && byRegion && ageDays > policy.retention_days && notOnHold;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you audit deletion correctness across millions of records?
- How would you handle privacy-rights requests that require immediate data erasure despite holds?
